A broadcast storm is when a NIC (or a port on a switch) sends out large amounts of broadcast traffic, thereby crippling network resources. 

RFI interruption refers to radio frequency interference: when an external radio source affects an electronic circuit.

 Wireshark is a network protocol analyzer. 

 Loopback is the routing of signals back to the source to test transmission and transportation infrastructure.